helpdesk-note.body: Tyler, Your account is not scheduled to disable. If you don't sign up for Spring classes it will disable in the second week of the Spring term. helpdesk-ticket.subject: Fw: LibGuides v2 Server IP has changed – your action is required
helpdesk-ticket.description:
________________________________ From: Helpdesk Sent: Wednesday, January 4, 2017 12:42 PM To: Desktech Subject: FW: LibGuides v2 Server IP has changed – your action is required
Peter Pfister
Help Desk Coordinator
414.277.7202
From: Gergetz, Denise Sent: Tuesday, January 03, 2017 2:24 PM To: Helpdesk <helpdesk@msoe.edu> Subject: FW: LibGuides v2 Server IP has changed – your action is required Importance: High
Hi IT,
Can you please update this for us as soon as possible? We migrated our content in LibGuides today and we need the DNS record changed to complete the update. Here’s the instructions from LibGuides. Please let me know if you have any questions.
1. Create a CNAME record for your custom LibGuides domain name on both your internal and external name servers. 2. Point these CNAME records to our LibGuides v2 server at: v2.libguides.com * Do not add your institution's name to this server address. Our server will map your domain name to your LibGuides site. * During the go-live process, which begins at 12pm U.S. Eastern time M-F (and runs on the hour after that, through 6pm), our servers will finish our side of the process: pointing to your specific site. * You will not see that this goes to your specific v2 site until this process runs. 3. Remove any old A or CNAME records for your LibGuides domain name. 4. Once your changes have propagated (which could take anywhere from a few minutes to several hours) and our part of the go-live process has run (to point to your specific site), your custom domain name will load your LibGuides v2 site.
Thanks,
Denise Gergetz, MLIS
Librarian II and Archivist
Walter Schroeder Library, L201
Milwaukee School of Engineering
414-277-7182
From: Cindi Blyberg [mailto:cindi@springshare.com] Sent: Tuesday, January 3, 2017 2:14 PM To: Cindi Blyberg <cindi@springshare.com<mailto:cindi@springshare.com>> Subject: LibGuides v2 Server IP has changed – your action is required
Hi, and Happy 2017 from your friends at Springshare!
We emailed you in early December to let you know that we were moving our LibApps & LibGuides v2 server to new infrastructure on December 30. The move went as planned, but we noticed that you haven’t yet updated your DNS records to reflect the change.
You must act ASAP and make this change by the end of the day January 6, 2017, because our old server will become unavailable shortly after that. Here’s the info that you need:
* Change your DNS A record for LibGuides into a CNAME Alias which points to v2.libguides.com<http://v2.libguides.com> (or update the A record IP to point to 34.194.39.199). We strongly recommend using a CNAME because this approach is more flexible.
As always, if you need assistance, just email us at support@springshare.com<mailto:support@springshare.com>. Thanks!
Best, -Cindi
—
Cindi Blyberg
Product Manager
Springshare - Easy to Use, Practical, Hosted Apps for Libraries
Follow Us on Twitter<http://www.twitter.com/springshare> | Like Us on Facebook<http://www.facebook.com/springshare> | Subscribe to our Blog<http://blog.springshare.com/>

Hi Kyle,
You are correct you need to be on premise to access adastra. But you could establish an on-prem connection by using the vpn (global protect). This software should be on most of our computers already.
You can use these instructions to install and configure it if it isn't setup yet.
http://msoe.freshservice.com/solution/categories/1000010350/folders/1000015760/articles/1000023935--how-do-i-install-and-use-globalprotect-windows-64bit-vpn-agent
The help desk can walk you through setup if you bring your computer in to them, or they can do it on the phone if you call 414-277-7288.
Tony

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Kyle Knoblauch,
If you want to come to the help desk for it you can at any time that we are open. Although setting up global protect isn't too difficult and you would need to connect to it every time you wish to use it off campus so we would just show you how to do it anyway. Otherwise if you want to save the trip, go into software center (search it in the windows search bar in the bottom left) search for global protect and install it. And then this link shows you everything you need to know as far as instructions for connecting whenever you need. Also if you can't find it or have trouble with software center there is a link within the first step of the instructions that is where you can also install global protect.
http://msoe.freshservice.com/solution/categories/1000010350/folders/1000015760/articles/1000023935--how-do-i-install-and-use-globalprotect-windows-64bit-vpn-agent
Of course you can always stop by the help desk and we will be happy to help you out at any time. Also with you being a staff member we have students working in Tier 2 Staff Support (myself included) that will gladly schedule times to come help you out with any technical problems that arise. If you have any other problems please let me know though the ticket or feel free to call me any time before 5pm and I will walk you through the steps of installing global protect. My number is in my response signature. Thanks, Kasey Horwath TIER 2 SUPPORT TEAM 414.277.2834 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu

I would like to request access to the Adobe Creative Cloud which contains this program. I understand we may have a campus subscription? Would you kindly let me know how we need to proceed? This project has been authorized by Dr. Bialek.
Thank you!

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Vivian Mickelson,
We currently have one license available. We do not have a campus license due to costs. An individual license is $420 a year. Do you have a budget number for the project? How long do you anticipate you'll need these licenses, as there is a monthly option available. Let me know. We are currently sorting out invoicing problems with our WAICU vendor, and so the one license was left unclaimed.
Thanks!

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hi Tim or Jazmine,
The finance charge report stored in the below location is not working properly. Every time I try to run it, it says the stored procedure needs @End_Date1. But when I run the old report it works fine. And I believe the new one was modified to not have a minimum dollar value for the charge.
Also, the stored procedure is not working correctly. When I ran the old report to see what it generates it actually created a negative finance charge, giving the students money. Not sure what it is calculating but I had to create an infomaker report that pulled all Subsid code A1, Subsid type 00, with a positive AR Balance to Date, and did not have the Suppress Finance Charge to be able to calculate it by hand.
[cid:image005.jpg@01D2678C.C0FD6500]

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Tom,
I'm focusing on this process and doing some testing. Just wanted to give you an update:
I asked you at one point about how and when we would clear finance charges (there is a column where all finance charges are added up and taken into account so that students aren't charged interest on interest). I wanted to let you know that there is a nightly job that clears those finance charges assessed when a student has a 0 or less than 0 AR posted balance, just an FYI. So I'm glad that is working. I will add that info to our Finance Charge report.
I have a quick question regarding the finance charge process. Once a student goes to collections, would we continue to add finance charges?
Jasmine

Once a student goes into collections they are placed in a separate Subsidiary Type code and would stop receiving finance charges.

helpdesk-ticket.description: There is no MSOEcert access point outside of S200 in the science building. Students go there to ask teachers questions on homework. helpdesk-ticket.description:
Helpdesk,
Me and my roommate in apt 412 of the MSOE tower have been having frequent connectivity issues to the internet since we moved back this week. I spoke to Rick Gagliano about the issue and they tried a reboot of the system to see if it fixed anything. When i tested it at 6AM this morning it seemed to have been fixed but by noon we had noticed the speeds drop considerably and my roommate reported issues loading websites (youtube, etc.) I have attached screenshots showing the connection speed differences with timestamps. It does not seem to matter if we are wired, using our local wireless hotspot, or the msoe or tower wireless hotspots, with the latter two being slower than the former.
I have run the test from multiple different computers as a check to make sure it isn’t something related to one of them. If you have any further testing ideas I can help with please let me know. I have CCed my roommate and Rick Gagliano to this email.
Thanks and hopefully we can figure this out, Michael Emch emchm@msoe.edu<mailto:emchm@msoe.edu>

helpdesk-ticket.subject: NAT Issues
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
I was wondering if someone could help me out with an issue I have been having with my xbox one connection as I am not knowledgeable on these sort of things. My internet is running fine and I have been able to connect to certain games before. However, I now have problems connecting to online game modes, such as in Grand Theft Auto, and can not use online party chat due to my "NAT Server Settings". My NAT is currently "unavailable", but a kid on my floor has his PlayStation NAT open. I can't imagine why these would be different and was wondering if there was anything I can do to solve the issue as I purchased this game and now cannot play it.
Thank you for your time,
Alexander Olson

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Anand Vyas, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/14509
So you are unable to click into the address bar and type anything at all? Does it freeze or not allow you to edit the address bar?
If all that works and the issue is just with the message "Your connection to this site is not secure", this occurs because the connection to the site is unencrypted and can be ignored. It is unencrypted because MSOE's website does not host a certificate to enable a secure HTTPS connection.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Kayla,
Your issue can occur if your connection to MSOE is slower than normal. Since this might be the case, it is strongly recommended that you increase network bandwidth (maybe get to a place with better bandwidth) or reduce latency to an acceptable level so the license management technology can function correctly.
If increasing network bandwidth is not an option, you can increase the amount of time the program waits for a response from the license manager by configuring an environment variable at the client workstation. Follow these steps to do that:
Right-click My Computer. Click Properties. Click the "Advanced system settings" link. In the System Properties dialog box, click the "Advanced" tab. On the Advanced tab, click "Environment Variables…". In the Environment Variables dialog box, under System Variables, click New. In the New System Variable dialog box, enter FLEXLM_TIMEOUT for the variable name and 1000000 for the variable value. Click OK to close each dialog box. Launch the Autodesk application.
If you are able to obtain a license, the value of 1000000 microseconds (1 second) is sufficient. If you still cannot obtain a license, repeat the procedure; increasing the value in 1000000 microsecond increments until you are able to obtain a license from the license server. If after several attempts, you still fail to get a valid license, please let Helpdesk know and we can look into this issue further for you. Thanks and have a great day! Regards, Xay Xiong MSOE IT Systems Administrator
---------------------------------------------
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Kayla, 

Your issue can occur if your connection to MSOE is slower than normal. Since this might be the case, it is strongly recommended that you increase network bandwidth (maybe get to a place with better bandwidth) or reduce latency to an acceptable level so the license management technology can function correctly.

If increasing network bandwidth is not an option, you can increase the amount of time the program waits for a response from the license manager by configuring an environment variable at the client workstation. Follow these steps to do that:
  1. Right-click My Computer. Click Properties. Click the "Advanced system settings" link.
  2. In the System Properties dialog box, click the "Advanced" tab.
  3. On the Advanced tab, click "Environment Variables…".
  4. In the Environment Variables dialog box, under System Variables, click New.
  5. In the New System Variable dialog box, enter FLEXLM_TIMEOUT for the variable name and 1000000 for the variable value.
  6. Click OK to close each dialog box.
  7. Launch the Autodesk application.
If you are able to obtain a license, the value of 1000000 microseconds (1 second) is sufficient. If you still cannot obtain a license, repeat the procedure; increasing the value in 1000000 microsecond increments until you are able to obtain a license from the license server.
If after several attempts, you still fail to get a valid license, please let Helpdesk know and we can look into this issue further for you.  Thanks and have a great day!
Regards,
Xay Xiong
MSOE IT Systems Administrator

---------------------------------------------

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/14517
 
From what I understand, this is an HP driver issue and shouldn't have anything to do with Outlook. If you want to ignore it it would be fine, but if you want it to stop happening the driver is either related to HP HotKey Support or the HP Quick Launch software. You can tell if you have HP Quick Launch if you see a blue question mark on the taskbar.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Internet settings
helpdesk-ticket.description: Hello, I recently found that my matlab opening problems are due to internet settings as on other students routers it works flawlessly and on wired connection it also works, do you happen to know what settings need to be changed to allow matlab licensing to know to validate and open?
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Hello, I recently found that my matlab opening problems are due to internet settings as on other students routers it works flawlessly and on wired connection it also works, do you happen to know what settings need to be changed to allow matlab licensing to know to validate and open?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jordyn Grande, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/14522
You have a couple of options, you can forward TCP port 27009 through you firewall, or you can simply add applicense2.msoe.edu (155.92.194.30). to the DMZ list on your router and that should also correct the issue. The user guide supplied with your router should explain the process. Please let us know if you have any issues.
Thanks,
Cameron Wilson Information Technology

helpdesk-ticket.description: i cant get any word docs to open. something about safe mode
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: i cant get any word docs to open. something about safe mode

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi John Hornburg,
I'm sorry to hear that you've been experiencing troubles with Microsoft Word. The following steps should allow you to exit safe mode. If the issues persist, please let us know via responding to this email or stop by the help desk. STEP 1 Open up a blank Word document on your computer. STEP 2 Click on the circular icon in the upper left-hand corner. Select "Word Options" from the menu. STEP 3 Click on "Trust Center" on the left-hand side of the menu. STEP 4 Select "Trust Center Settings." STEP 5 Select the "Active X Settings" and uncheck the box for "Safe Mode." This will disable the feature in all Office programs. STEP 6 Hit "OK" to save your changes and close the Microsoft Word document. These steps were found at the following link: source
Respectfully, Sabrina Stangler TIER 1 SUPPORT TEAM 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Twitter : @MSOEIT
"We are building a culture of Exceptional Customer Service"

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Error on Library Staff Printer
helpdesk-ticket.description: Staff Printer HP Laserjet 4050TN in the library is giving an error. User was attempting to print from Microsoft Access.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Staff Printer HP Laserjet 4050TN in the library is giving an error. User was attempting to print from Microsoft Access.

helpdesk-note.body: Fixed, will write up more detailed note when I get back to IT
helpdesk-note.body-html: Fixed, will write up more detailed note when I get back to IT

helpdesk-note.body:
Went over to look at printer. The librarian had already tried power cycling the printer and the laptop.
When a librarian sent a print job to the printer from their laptop, it would seem to send correctly, it would show up correctly in the printer queue as "Printing", but the printer would not do anything and about a minute later the print job would change to "Error - Printing". I tried reinstalling the printer but the installer could not find the IP address. I looked through the printer's settings and noticed that the network configuration had gotten disabled, so I enabled that and then was able to reinstall the printer on the laptop, which I tested by printing a test page, which worked.
I set the new printer as the default printer and verified functionality with the document that was failing.
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Went over to look at printer. The librarian had already tried power cycling the printer and the laptop.

When a librarian sent a print job to the printer from their laptop, it would seem to send correctly, it would show up correctly in the printer queue as "Printing", but the printer would not do anything and about a minute later the print job would change to "Error - Printing". I tried reinstalling the printer but the installer could not find the IP address. I looked through the printer's settings and noticed that the network configuration had gotten disabled, so I enabled that and then was able to reinstall the printer on the laptop, which I tested by printing a test page, which worked.

I set the new printer as the default printer and verified functionality with the document that was failing.

Hi Roberto Rojas, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/14544 We actually do not schedule appointments for applying grad images and laptop gifting, so feel free to stop by anytime. helpdesk-note.body:
Hi John Hornburg, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/14546 If you have not already done so, just try downloading and installing again. Trying downloading it at the helpdesk on multiple machines, we had no troubles. Have you ever used any other Citrix software on this machine? If so, that may be interfering with the GoToMeeting installer. It is also possible that you are not an administrator on your laptop, which would require you to come to the desk. If after removing any other Citrix files and trying the process again you are still unable to successfully download GoToMeeting, please stop by the helpdesk and we'll troubleshoot from there. Our hours are 730-7 Monday-Thursday, 730-5 Friday, and 10-6 Saturday-Sunday.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Tablet Does Not Connect To Printer
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello, Even though I was just over there and had you map my stupid tablet to the General Studies printer, it still won't let me print. It says "access denied" unable to connect.
What are my options?
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello,
Even though I was just over there and had you map my stupid tablet to the General Studies printer, it still won't let me print.  It says "access denied" unable to connect.

What are my options?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Jennifer Farrell, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/14560
Can you please check and make sure you are not connected the MSOE-Guest network. If you are, please try connecting to MSOEcert or MSOE.
If this is not the issue, I would recommend reinstalling the printer. To do this please go to Devices and Printers, right click on the general studies printer you are trying to print to, and select Remove Device. After this you can reinstall the printer by going to the start menu at the bottom left hand corner of the screen, type \\printers, and double click on the printer you need. Finally, click ok if it asks to install a drive and you should be able to print to the general studies printer.
Please let us know if this works or not.
Respectfully, Savanah Cleveland TIER 1 SUPPORT TEAM 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Twitter : @MSOEIT
"We are building a culture of Exceptional Customer Service"

Hi Jennifer Farrell,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/14560

Can you please check and make sure you are not connected the MSOE-Guest network. If you are, please try connecting to MSOEcert or MSOE. 

If this is not the issue, I would recommend reinstalling the printer. To do this please go to Devices and Printers, right click on the general studies printer you are trying to print to, and select Remove Device. After this you can reinstall the printer by going to the start menu at the bottom left hand corner of the screen, type \\printers, and double click on the printer you need. Finally, click ok if it asks to install a drive and you should be able to print to the general studies printer. 

Please let us know if this works or not.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi John Hornburg, It sounds like your Outlook needs to be repaired.
1. Just go to Control Panel>Programs>Programs And Features. 2. Scroll down to "Microsoft Office", right click on it and click "change". 3. A dialog box should open and from there select "Repair". 4. Click "Continue" and then wait for it to finish.
Note: Close all Office programs before repairing I.E. Outlook, Word, Excel, etc.
If this doesn't work let us know and we'll see what we can do from there.
Respectfully, Mitch Paulsen
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi John Hornburg,

It sounds like your Outlook needs to be repaired.

1. Just go to Control Panel>Programs>Programs And Features.
2. Scroll down to "Microsoft Office", right click on it and click "change".
3. A dialog box should open and from there select "Repair".
4. Click "Continue" and then wait for it to finish.

Note: Close all Office programs before repairing I.E. Outlook, Word, Excel, etc.

If this doesn't work let us know and we'll see what we can do from there.

Respectfully,
Mitch Paulsen

helpdesk-ticket.description:
My computer will not send powerpoint print requests to the printer, it will only send microsoft word prints.

helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
My computer will not send powerpoint print requests to the printer, it will only send microsoft word prints.

I'm connected to MSOE wifi and connected with Global protect... I'm currently on campus, so not sure why it's no longer connecting. I did not have this issue yesterday. I did change my password recently

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Leah Ruplinger, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/14579
In order to print, you need to be connected to an MSOE wireless network, not Guest, which it sounds like you are. Please try checking the size of the page you are trying to print because if it is not the standard size of the printer paper it will not print. If it is irregular, try going to File>Options in Powerpoint and scroll down to "When printing this document" and make sure the "Use the following print settings" and "Scale to fit paper" boxes are checked. If this doesn't work, please try saving the document as a PDF and printing from Adobe. If this method works as opposed to printing from Powerpoint it could indicate that something is wrong with Powerpoint and I would recommend bringing your computer to the desk where we can troubleshoot that issue. Please let us know what works for you, if anything, or if you require more assistance.
Respectfully, Amanda Goff TIER 1 SUPPORT TEAM 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Twitter : @MSOEIT
"We are building a culture of Exceptional Customer Service"

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Briggsa, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/14586
I'm sorry that you're having this issue, if you'd like we can try a couple of things to get it working for you again.
The first would be for you to force the WiFi receiver to refresh, and you can do this by pressing the WiFi enabling button at the top right corner of your keyboard to disable WiFi, wait about ten seconds, and turn it back on.
If this doesn't work you can also try another way of refreshing the receiver by disabling WiFi again like above, turning your laptop off, and plugging an ethernet cord in, then turning the laptop back on. See if it connects to the internet through the cord and if it does then you can unplug the ethernet cord and turn the WiFi back on.
If neither of these work could you please just reply answering a few questions for me so that we could better help you? When did this start happening? Where were you and does it happen everywhere? Can you connect to any other WiFi networks? Or is it just MSOEcert?
Thank you!
Respectfully, Karolina Klimont TIER 1 SUPPORT TEAM 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Twitter : @MSOEIT
"We are building a culture of Exceptional Customer Service"

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Catherine Trice,
Hope this email finds you well. As per MSOE policy, all graduate students are to have their computers grad-imaged by IT. During this process the computer will also be marked as gifted and will avoid all legal issues in the future.
After talking to my manager, he suggested that you either come to Milwaukee to get this done or that you mail the laptop to us and we will mail it back after the process is done. Unfortunately, we do not have any alternatives at this moment. The mailing address is: MSOE IT DEPARTMENT - 1025 N Broadway, Milwaukee WI, 53202.
If you have any questions, please feel free to ask.
Respectfully, Alwin M Abraham TIER 1 SUPPORT TEAM 414.277.7288 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu Twitter : @MSOEIT
"We are building a culture of Exceptional Customer Service"

helpdesk-note.body: I tried to do this as well and it didn't work. A pop-up said that there were no servers for @msoe.edu
helpdesk-note.body-html: I tried to do this as well and it didn't work. A pop-up said that there were no servers for @msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mike Cordes,
Skype for Business is not part of our base image. It appears to be something that was added by Microsoft in an update. We've checked several Windows 7 machines that have images from when Skype for Business was still called Microsoft Lync, and they also have it installed. This isn't something that we have deployed, so there won't be any servers on our domain that will authenticate your credentials.
Thanks,
Paul Fabian

helpdesk-note.body:
The 1098-T pbl they are asking for has forms and a report that will help them remove errors when trying to generate 1098-Ts. Added the pbl from MyJenzabar and was prompted to migrate the pbl. I received the following error 'C0193: One or more of the files in your library list could not be opened for write.'
There was an answer available in the Jenzabar support portal:
Resolution: To get past this error you will need to go to File, Library List. Highlight the text and copy it to notepad. The delete it from the library list window. Create your executable and it should no longer give this error message. Then once you have the executable created, copy the information back into the library list and save. You just can't have those libraries in the library list when you try to create the executable because those libraries are read only and it throws that error.
helpdesk-note.body-html:

I received the following error 'C0193: One or more of the files in your library list could not be opened for write.'

There was an answer available in the Jenzabar support portal:
Resolution:
To get past this error you will need to go to File, Library List. Highlight the text and copy it to notepad. The delete it from the library list window. Create your executable and it should no longer give this error message. 
Then once you have the executable created, copy the information back into the library list and save. You just can't have those libraries in the library list when you try to create the executable because those libraries are read only and it throws that error.

helpdesk-note.body-html: Allison called in this morning saying she wants the Mondo Pad fixed before 1:00 because it's being used for presentations over the weekend. I can take a look at it today.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Allison Raison,
I stopped by and got the sound working. Since you wanted to know the steps taken place to fix the issue and I came too late to catch you while you were there, I will include the steps I took to fix the issue. I found out that in the TV settings (accessed by the TV remote/buttons directly on the TV) someone had changed the sound input to something different. It was also pretty sneaky because there were 2 different inputs that had "PC" in them. It was set on one that had "PC something else" when it should have been on the setting that was only "PC" as an option. For future reference the setting for that is in the Menu and it is the third box down. Then there is an option saying "sound input". If you have any other questions please let me know. I will mark the ticket resolved as the sound now works perfectly fine. Have a great weekend Thanks, Kasey Horwath TIER 2 SUPPORT TEAM 414.277.2834 Submit a Service Request: helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.description: The cisco phone in the public safety office is having connection issues with the receiver cord. Another issue is the phone not always allowing the release of calls that are on hold.

helpdesk-note.body:
i have a handset and cord on my desk to swap I will send a student worker by with it shortly.
Looks like held calls can be picked up by hitting the line button, which should be flashing green, or by hitting the resume soft button along the bottom of the screen.
If the remote user hangs up the line should stop blinking.
http://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/cuipph/8941_8945/8_5/english/qsg/QSG_8941_8945_en_851.pdf
This document states that you shouldn't hit hold to resume held calls though it does seem to work, i assume there is a reason they say it doesn't.
Let me know if this hold issue persists as its possible i can change some things in the phone setup to make the calls more robust.

i have a handset and cord on my desk to swap I will send a student worker by with it shortly.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: ANSYS on the Blade Server
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I got an email from Vivian Mickelson the other day, saying that we needed to have ANSYS updated to the current version on the Blade server. In order to be able to do so, we needed to close all of our design softwares for a four-hour time block.
We have been waiting 24-hours already, with everything ready on our end, and ANSYS 15.0 is still installed, instead of ANSYS 17.0. Seeing as we need this software and the servers for our senior design project, which has a deadline, we cannot keep waiting for this update. I know that there are other senior design groups that need this new version of ANSYS, so this is a very high priority issue.
I look forward to hearing back from you guys, so we can get this all sorted out ASAP.
-- [https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/KIx9plklmtltS5CePidODeoZ_tNg6stcPfsp6ap048uHmDRECSBokLew9ByKEnCOdR3HTdSsv4EJ4EDn3h375Y-NvzwdATRcGcffYDYuz8dRlaODh8qPg9JnHylr6y4OnS2Fs2Y] Zachary Ptasienski Milwaukee School of Engineering – BSME 2017 (*pursuant) Delta Sigma Phi Fraternity, Eta Alpha Chapter – New Member Educator Cigar and Pipe Social Club at MSOE – Chief
